# Autonomous Advent of Code solver — {{YEAR}} Day {{DAY}}

You have full autonomy to solve today's puzzle end-to-end. Use the shell tools below.
Loop until both parts are accepted (or Part 1 only in dry-run mode).

## Toolkit

All commands run from the repo root:

```bash
uv run python scripts/aoc_tool.py prepare      # fetch input + puzzle text from AoC
uv run python scripts/aoc_tool.py meta         # day, year, solution paths
uv run python scripts/aoc_tool.py input-path   # path to your puzzle input file
uv run python scripts/aoc_tool.py puzzle 1     # Part 1 description
uv run python scripts/aoc_tool.py puzzle 2     # Part 2 (only after Part 1 accepted on AoC)
uv run python scripts/aoc_tool.py test 1       # run solutions/{{YEAR}}/{{DAY}}/part1.py
uv run python scripts/aoc_tool.py test 2       # run part2.py
uv run python scripts/aoc_tool.py submit 1     # submit Part 1 to adventofcode.com
uv run python scripts/aoc_tool.py submit 2     # submit Part 2
uv run python scripts/aoc_tool.py refresh      # re-fetch page after Part 1 unlocks Part 2
```

{{DRY_RUN_SECTION}}

## Solution files

Write one file per part under `solutions/{{YEAR}}/{{DAY}}/`:

- `solutions/{{YEAR}}/{{DAY}}/part1.py`
- `solutions/{{YEAR}}/{{DAY}}/part2.py`

Each file must define:

```python
def solve(data: str) -> str:
    ...
```

- Standard library only.
- Read input from the `data` argument (never hardcode answers).
- Do **not** read `AOC_SESSION` or any secrets — `submit` handles auth.

Run `prepare` first — it creates the `solutions/{{YEAR}}/{{DAY}}/` directory.

## Required workflow

1. `prepare` → read `meta` and `puzzle 1`.
2. Implement `part1.py` in the solution directory.
3. **Loop** until `test 1` passes.
4. {{SUBMIT_PART1_SECTION}}
5. `refresh` → confirm `meta` shows `"has_part2": true` → `puzzle 2`.
6. Implement `part2.py` (keep part1 working).
7. **Loop** until `test 2` passes.
8. {{SUBMIT_PART2_SECTION}}
9. Stop when done. Summarize both answers and submission results.

## Rules

- AoC rate-limits submissions to ~1/minute — if submit says rate limited, wait and retry.
- If submit returns WRONG, read the feedback, fix the code, `test` again, then `submit` again.
- Part 2 text is **not** available until Part 1 is accepted on adventofcode.com.
- Test locally before every submit.
